parameters.name: UnloadedComponentPathNames
parameters.description: Array of the paths of the unloaded components

parameters.name: UnloadedComponentReferencedConfigurationNames
parameters.description: Array of the referenced configuration names of the unloaded components

title: IAssemblyDoc.GetUnloadedComponentNames
description: Gets the unloaded components' paths, referenced configuration names, reasons why they are unloaded, document types, and names.
signature:
System.Object GetUnloadedComponentNames( 
   out System.Object
UnloadedComponentPathNames
,
   out System.Object
UnloadedComponentReferencedConfigurationNames
,
   out System.Object
ReasonForUnloadingComponents
,
   out System.Object
DocTypes
)

parameters.name: UnloadedComponentPathNames
parameters.description: Array of the paths of the unloaded components

parameters.name: UnloadedComponentReferencedConfigurationNames
parameters.description: Array of the referenced configuration names of the unloaded components

parameters.name: ReasonForUnloadingComponents
parameters.description: Array indicating the reason each component is unloaded as defined by swComponentLoadStatus_e

parameters.name: DocTypes
parameters.description: Array of document types as defined in swDocumentTypes_e

returns: Array of the names of the unloaded components
remarks:
This method is useful when the assembly document was opened with
Quick View/Selective open
or
Do not load hidden components
.
To get whether an assembly has hidden or suppressed unloaded components, call
IAssemblyDoc::HasUnloadedComponents
.
